        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>RTP Full Funding Act of 202</b><strong>1</strong></p> <p>This bill revises provisions regarding the recreational trails program of the Department of Transportation (DOT).</p> <p>Specifically, the bill requires</p> <ul> <li>DOT to estimate the total amount of nonhighway recreational fuel taxes received by the Department of the Treasury and transferred to the Highway Trust Fund;</li> <li>the Federal Highway Administration to establish financial management information system codes for certain motorized and non-motorized use projects, including single and diverse use projects;</li> <li>DOT to reserve amounts of the state-apportioned funds for administrative, research, technical assistance, and training expenses to carry out the recreational trails program; and</li> <li>states to obligate a specific amount of reserved funds each fiscal year for the recreational trails program.</li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
